TASK 7: Merge Branches - Terminal Output
================================================================================

COMMANDS AND OUTPUT:
================================================================================

$ git checkout main
Switched to branch 'main'
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

$ git merge bug-fix-typo
Updating abc1234..def5678
Fast-forward
 README.md | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

================================================================================
DETAILED EXPLANATION:
================================================================================

Command 1: git checkout main
   $ git checkout main
   Switched to branch 'main'
   Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.
   
   Explanation:
   - This command switches from the current branch to the 'main' branch
   - The message confirms you are now on the main branch
   - It shows that the main branch is up to date with the remote origin

Command 2: git merge bug-fix-typo
   $ git merge bug-fix-typo
   Updating abc1234..def5678
   Fast-forward
    README.md | 1 +
    1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)
   
   Explanation:
   - This command merges the 'bug-fix-typo' branch into the current 'main' branch
   - "Updating abc1234..def5678" shows the commit range being merged
   - "Fast-forward" indicates a fast-forward merge (no merge commit needed)
   - "README.md | 1 +" shows that README.md file had 1 insertion
   - "1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)" confirms that 1 file was modified with 1 line added

================================================================================
STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS TO COMPLETE TASK 7:
================================================================================

Step 1: Clone your forked repository (if not already done)
   $ git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/mcino-Introduction-to-Git-and-GitHub.git
   $ cd mcino-Introduction-to-Git-and-GitHub

Step 2: Create the bug-fix-typo branch (if not already created)
   $ git checkout -b bug-fix-typo

Step 3: Make a change to fix a typo
   Edit README.md and fix a typo, for example:
   
   Before: "Introdution to Git and GitHub"
   After:  "Introduction to Git and GitHub"
   
   Save the file.

Step 4: Stage and commit your changes
   $ git add README.md
   $ git commit -m "Fix: Correct typo in README.md"

Step 5: Push the branch to your fork
   $ git push origin bug-fix-typo

Step 6: Switch back to the main branch
   $ git checkout main
   Switched to branch 'main'
   Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

Step 7: Merge the bug-fix-typo branch into main
   $ git merge bug-fix-typo
   Updating abc1234..def5678
   Fast-forward
    README.md | 1 +
    1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

Step 8: Copy the output from steps 6 and 7
   Save the output to a file named 'merge_branches'

================================================================================
EXPECTED OUTPUT FORMAT:
================================================================================

The output should show:
1. "Switched to branch 'main'" - confirming checkout was successful
2. "git merge bug-fix-typo" - the merge command
3. "Updating [commit_hash]..[commit_hash]" - commit range
4. "Fast-forward" or "Merge made by..." - merge type
5. "README.md | 1 +" - the file that was changed
6. "1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)" - summary showing 1 file changed

