================================================================================
WHAT EACH PART OF THE OUTPUT MEANS:
================================================================================

1. "Switched to branch 'main'"
   - Confirms successful checkout to main branch

2. "Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'"
   - Your local main is synchronized with the remote

3. "Updating abc1234..def5678"
   - Shows the commit range being merged
   - abc1234 = commit before merge
   - def5678 = commit being merged in

4. "Fast-forward"
   - Type of merge where main branch pointer moves to the new commit
   - No merge commit is created
   - Happens when no conflicting changes were made

5. " README.md | 1 +"
   - File name: README.md
   - 1 + means 1 line was added
   - (A '-' would mean lines were removed)

6. "1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)"
   - Total summary: 1 file was modified
   - 1 insertion means 1 line was added

================================================================================
IMPORTANT NOTES:
================================================================================

1. The exact commit hashes (abc1234, def5678) will be different for your repo
2. You can view these hashes by running: git log --oneline
3. The merge type might be "Fast-forward" or "Merge made by 'recursive' strategy"
   depending on your branch history
4. The important part for Task 7 is: "1 file changed" which proves the merge worked
5. After the merge, you can push to origin: git push origin main

================================================================================
TROUBLESHOOTING:
================================================================================

If you see "Already up to date":
   - This means the branches are already merged
   - Create a new change on bug-fix-typo branch and try again

If you see merge conflict:
   - Resolve the conflict in the editor
   - Run: git add . && git commit -m "Merge: Resolve conflicts"

If you see "fatal: Not a valid object name":
   - The branch might not exist
   - Create it first: git checkout -b bug-fix-typo

================================================================================
VERIFICATION:
================================================================================

To verify the merge was successful, run:
   $ git log --oneline -n 5
   
This will show the recent commits including your merge.

Also verify the file was changed:
   $ git diff HEAD~1 README.md
   
This will show the changes made in the merge.

